SWORN: Signed Workflow Of Reasoned Narratives
Copyright 2026 Jonathan

This product includes software developed as a personal entry to the
SANS Find Evil! hackathon (June 2026).

Built on Protocol SIFT (https://github.com/teamdfir/protocol-sift)
by Rob T. Lee and the SANS DFIR community.

Architectural inspiration from Valhuntir (https://github.com/AppliedIR/Valhuntir)
by Steve Anson.

Uses the following third-party tools, each under its own license, called via
typed wrappers in this project:

  Volatility 3 (Volatility Foundation, Volatility Software License 1.0)
  plaso / log2timeline / psort (Apache 2.0)
  Eric Zimmerman tools - EvtxECmd, MFTECmd, RECmd, PECmd (MIT)
  Hayabusa (GPL-3.0)
  RegRipper (GPL-3.0)
  The Sleuth Kit (CPL / IBM Public License / GPL)
  bulk_extractor (public domain)
  YARA (BSD 3-Clause)
  Hindsight (Apache 2.0)
  Florian Roth signature-base YARA rules (CC BY-NC 4.0; SWORN ships none of
    these rules in this repo and downloads them at install time only if the
    operator accepts the upstream license)
